  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its excessive height and depth along the shared boundary with no. 29 Forburg Road, would have a significant and harmful impact on the amenities enjoyed by residents of this property, particularly in regard to loss of daylight/sunlight, loss of outlook and an increased sense of enclosure. The proposed development is therefore unacceptable and fails to comply with policies LP1 and LP2 of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the stipulations of the council&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its inappropriate roof design and excessive bulk, particularly in regard to height, would result in an inappropriate and incongruous form of development that would detract from the original design of the host property and would detract from the character of this part of Northwold &amp;amp; Cazenove Conservation Area. The proposed development is considered unacceptable in regard to design and fails to comply with policies D3, D4, and HC1 of the London Plan (2021) policies LP1, LP2, and LP3 of the Hackney Local Plan (2020), and the stipulations of the council&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&lt;/p&gt;"
